==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: adsorption
<hw>adsorption</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>the
process by which molecules of a substance form a thin film on the
surface of a solid. Distinguished from <contr>absorption</contr>, in
which the foreign substance penetrates the body of the absorbing
material.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> surface assimilation</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>adsorptive</ent>⟦br⟧
